J. O. SPAULDING, Appellant, v. Joseph W. SANFORD, Warden, United States Penitentiary, Atlanta, Georgia, Appellee. No. 9856. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. May 28, 1941. J. O. Spaulding, in pro. per., for appellant. Lawrence S. Camp, U. S. Atty., and Harvey II. Tysinger, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Atlanta, Ga., for appellee.

Before FOSTER, HUTCHESON, and HOLMES, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
